Circumstance.Other: 84 y/o male from CRCC SAGE unit with PMHx significant for DM, HTN, A-fib, anemia and squamous cell carcinoma to scalp.  He tested positive for COVID on 10/14 and was transferred to WSP IPU for NPR isolation.  Patient was cleared from COVID isolation on 10/23 but remained with significant decompensation and with failure to thrive, he was not wanting to eat or drink much at all.  The patient refused further workup, diagnostics or to be sent to local ER for higher level of care.  Patient updated his POLST requesting again to be DNR but changed medical management to comfort focused treatment (vs full treatment).  He refused hospice to come in and see him but did agree to end of life/comfort care in   the IPU, a seriously ill notification was submitted.  Patient has continued with comfort care in the IPU. This morning, I was notified by nursing that the patient appeared to be deceased.  I was able to confirm absence of pulse and respirations; time of death was noted at 0714 hrs.

Circumstance.Specific: Malignant neoplasms (cancer); Chronic liver disease and cirrhosis
Circumstance.Other: Patient with hepatocellular carcinoma, had opted out of further treatment, discussed with primary  provider, as disease progression occurred, he opted to transition to palliative and comfort care measures and was admitted to the infirmary (IPU) on 4/26/2024.  He was declining steadily and palliation of pain  was achieved with medical therapies.  Family was kept informed of his decision and once admitted to     IPU family visits were arranged, taking place on 5/3/2024 and 5/4/2024.  Afterward he declined very   rapidly and within 1 day was no longer taking food or fluids in any significant amount.  A final family visit occurred on 5/8/2024, in IPU, at which time the  FMD (Facility Medical Director) met with the family, he  was unresponsive to them at that time and passed away peacefully approximately 6 hours later.

Circumstance.Other:
This patient had end stage COPD with frequent exacerbations and pneumonia.  On 8/22/24 the patient
was tachypneic, hypotensive, and had an increase oxygen need and was sent to the hospital via EMS.  He remained admitted until the time of his death.

Patient passed away on palliative care measures at Harborview Medical Center in Seattle, WA, after self-
asphyxiation event in cell on 7/18/2024.
Found unresponsive in cell; CPR performed; Paramedics pronounced dead at 13:15; no transport.
